content:
Specify Context Mapping Intent to Use Different Mapping Types

Perform the Association, Hydration, Persistence and Translation operations to support one-to-one, one-to-many, many-to-one, and cross attribute mappings. Based on the intent operation you select, the mapping type changes. Previously, only one-to-one attribute mapping was available to perform the Hydration and Persistence operation.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience in Professional, Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer editions for Industries clouds where Context Service is enabled.

How: Open the context definition that you want to add the mapping to. On the Context Definition Details page, click the Map Data tab. Click Add Mapping. On the Add Context Mapping window, enter Name, click Next. On the Mapping Intent Details window, select the mapping intent operation.
title: Specify Context Mapping Intent for Different Mappings
